    • Field Detail

      • DEFAULT_INCLUDE_INFERENCES

        public static final java.lang.Boolean DEFAULT_INCLUDE_INFERENCES
        The default value for including also inferences on queries response (see: isIncludingInferences()).

      • DEFAULT_RETURN_COMPLETE_DESCRIPTION

        public static final java.lang.Boolean DEFAULT_RETURN_COMPLETE_DESCRIPTION
        Boolean used to query the reasoner sub/super-(class or properties). If it is false only hierarchically direct entities will be returned (all non-reasoned values are returned anyway). Else, it collects all entities up to the leafs and root of the structure (see: isReturningCompleteDescription()).

      • isIncludingInferences

        public java.lang.Boolean isIncludingInferences()
        It is True if this OWLEnquirer is also appending inferred axioms to the queries. If it is set to false it enables/disables the effects of isIncludingInferences(), since no reasoning processes are involved.
        This flag is not considered on sparql(String, Long) and derived methods, which always relies on the reasoner.
        Returns:
        false if the queries consider only asserted axioms.

      • setIncludeInferences

        public void setIncludeInferences(boolean includesInferences)
        Set to false if the queries consider only asserted axioms. Set to true to get also inferred axioms
        Parameters:
        includesInferences - the flag to indicate if this.{@link #isIncludingInferences()}.

      • getIndividualB2Thing

        public java.util.Set<org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual> getIndividualB2Thing()
        Returns all individual defined in the ontology OWLVocabularyProvider.getOWLThing(). It returns null if no individuals belong to the root class or if such class does not exist. Results completeness is ensured only if returnsCompleteDescription is set to true.
        Returns:
        individuals belonging to the root class of the ontology.

        Performs a SPARQL query on the ontology. Returns a list of QuerySolution or null if the query fails.         query - a string defining the query in SPARQL query syntax.
        timeOut - timeout for the query (not all query support it).
        Returns:
        list of solutions.
